President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring May 15-21, 2016 as World Trade Week. In the proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of global trade and its role in creating jobs and growing the economy. He highlights the need for smart trade agreements that benefit American workers and businesses, and mentions the Trans-Pacific Partnership (TPP) as a trade deal that promotes American values and supports good jobs. Obama also mentions the Trans-Atlantic Trade and Investment Partnership (T-TIP), which aims to eliminate barriers and strengthen trade and investment between the United States and the European Union. The proclamation encourages Americans to participate in events and programs that celebrate and educate about the benefits of trade.